# Version honesty

## Stable installs

Pin user-facing install examples to the **latest stable tag** (`v2.2.0` as of July 2026):

- Docker: `prest/prest:v2.2.0`
- Go: `go install github.com/prest/prest/v2/cmd/prestd@v2.2.0`

Do not leave install paths on older stable tags while hubs advertise a newer release.

Feature gates can still say “v2.1.0+” (MCP) or “v2.2.0+” (Studio, database-backed queries) when describing when a feature landed.

## Unreleased `main`

Features only on `prest/prest` main (not yet tagged) must be labeled:

- `{% hint style="warning" %}` **Requires prest `main` (unreleased)** + PR link
- Never claim they ship in a tag they are not on

Claim upgrade/install steps only for tagged releases. See `write-docs` voice do-not-claim.
